cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.CG, cs.DM. 

The paper involves analysis of a game involving tiles and merges, which suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of a min-max theorem and the analysis of optimal strategies suggest a connection to game theory (cs.GT). The use of change-making algorithms and the connection to binary and Fibonacci representations suggest a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and combinatorial algorithms (cs.CG). Finally, the analysis of the termination of the game suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
